ontology_info.name: PROV Ontology
ontology_info.description: W3C Provenance Ontology for representing provenance information

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#ActivityInflue.label: ActivityInfluence
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#ActivityInflue.description: ActivityInfluence provides additional descriptions of an Activity's binary influence upon any other kind of resource. Instances of ActivityInfluence use the prov:activity property to cite the influencing Activity.

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#AgentInfluence.label: AgentInfluence
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#AgentInfluence.description: AgentInfluence provides additional descriptions of an Agent's binary influence upon any other kind of resource. Instances of AgentInfluence use the prov:agent property to cite the influencing Agent.

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Association.label: Association
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Association.description: An instance of prov:Association provides additional descriptions about the binary prov:wasAssociatedWith relation from an prov:Activity to some prov:Agent that had some responsiblity for it. For example, :baking prov:wasAssociatedWith :baker; prov:qualifiedAssociation [ a prov:Association; prov:agent :baker; :foo :bar ].

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Attribution.label: Attribution
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Attribution.description: An instance of prov:Attribution provides additional descriptions about the binary prov:wasAttributedTo relation from an prov:Entity to some prov:Agent that had some responsible for it. For example, :cake prov:wasAttributedTo :baker; prov:qualifiedAttribution [ a prov:Attribution; prov:entity :baker; :foo :bar ].

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Bundle.label: Bundle
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Bundle.description: Note that there are kinds of bundles (e.g. handwritten letters, audio recordings, etc.) that are not expressed in PROV-O, but can be still be described by PROV-O.

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Communication.label: Communication
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Communication.description: An instance of prov:Communication provides additional descriptions about the binary prov:wasInformedBy relation from an informed prov:Activity to the prov:Activity that informed it. For example, :you_jumping_off_bridge prov:wasInformedBy :everyone_else_jumping_off_bridge; prov:qualifiedCommunication [ a prov:Communication; prov:activity :everyone_else_jumping_off_bridge; :foo :bar ].

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Delegation.label: Delegation
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Delegation.description: An instance of prov:Delegation provides additional descriptions about the binary prov:actedOnBehalfOf relation from a performing prov:Agent to some prov:Agent for whom it was performed. For example, :mixing prov:wasAssociatedWith :toddler . :toddler prov:actedOnBehalfOf :mother; prov:qualifiedDelegation [ a prov:Delegation; prov:entity :mother; :foo :bar ].

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Derivation.label: Derivation
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Derivation.description: An instance of prov:Derivation provides additional descriptions about the binary prov:wasDerivedFrom relation from some derived prov:Entity to another prov:Entity from which it was derived. For example, :chewed_bubble_gum prov:wasDerivedFrom :unwrapped_bubble_gum; prov:qualifiedDerivation [ a prov:Derivation; prov:entity :unwrapped_bubble_gum; :foo :bar ].

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#End.label: End
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#End.description: An instance of prov:End provides additional descriptions about the binary prov:wasEndedBy relation from some ended prov:Activity to an prov:Entity that ended it. For example, :ball_game prov:wasEndedBy :buzzer; prov:qualifiedEnd [ a prov:End; prov:entity :buzzer; :foo :bar; prov:atTime '2012-03-09T08:05:08-05:00'^^xsd:dateTime ].

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#EntityInfluenc.label: EntityInfluence
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#EntityInfluenc.description: EntityInfluence provides additional descriptions of an Entity's binary influence upon any other kind of resource. Instances of EntityInfluence use the prov:entity property to cite the influencing Entity.

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Generation.label: Generation
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Generation.description: An instance of prov:Generation provides additional descriptions about the binary prov:wasGeneratedBy relation from a generated prov:Entity to the prov:Activity that generated it. For example, :cake prov:wasGeneratedBy :baking; prov:qualifiedGeneration [ a prov:Generation; prov:activity :baking; :foo :bar ].

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Influence.label: Influence
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Influence.description: An instance of prov:Influence provides additional descriptions about the binary prov:wasInfluencedBy relation from some influenced Activity, Entity, or Agent to the influencing Activity, Entity, or Agent. For example, :stomach_ache prov:wasInfluencedBy :spoon; prov:qualifiedInfluence [ a prov:Influence; prov:entity :spoon; :foo :bar ] . Because prov:Influence is a broad relation, the more specific relations (Communication, Delegation, End, etc.) should be used when applicable.

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#InstantaneousE.label: InstantaneousEvent
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#InstantaneousE.description: An instantaneous event, or event for short, happens in the world and marks a change in the world, in its activities and in its entities. The term 'event' is commonly used in process algebra with a similar meaning. Events represent communications or interactions; they are assumed to be atomic and instantaneous.

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Invalidation.label: Invalidation
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Invalidation.description: An instance of prov:Invalidation provides additional descriptions about the binary prov:wasInvalidatedBy relation from an invalidated prov:Entity to the prov:Activity that invalidated it. For example, :uncracked_egg prov:wasInvalidatedBy :baking; prov:qualifiedInvalidation [ a prov:Invalidation; prov:activity :baking; :foo :bar ].

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Plan.label: Plan
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Plan.description: There exist no prescriptive requirement on the nature of plans, their representation, the actions or steps they consist of, or their intended goals. Since plans may evolve over time, it may become necessary to track their provenance, so plans themselves are entities. Representing the plan explicitly in the provenance can be useful for various tasks: for example, to validate the execution as represented in the provenance record, to manage expectation failures, or to provide explanations.

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#PrimarySource.label: PrimarySource
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#PrimarySource.description: An instance of prov:PrimarySource provides additional descriptions about the binary prov:hadPrimarySource relation from some secondary prov:Entity to an earlier, primary prov:Entity. For example, :blog prov:hadPrimarySource :newsArticle; prov:qualifiedPrimarySource [ a prov:PrimarySource; prov:entity :newsArticle; :foo :bar ] .

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Quotation.label: Quotation
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Quotation.description: An instance of prov:Quotation provides additional descriptions about the binary prov:wasQuotedFrom relation from some taken prov:Entity from an earlier, larger prov:Entity. For example, :here_is_looking_at_you_kid prov:wasQuotedFrom :casablanca_script; prov:qualifiedQuotation [ a prov:Quotation; prov:entity :casablanca_script; :foo :bar ].

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Revision.label: Revision
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Revision.description: An instance of prov:Revision provides additional descriptions about the binary prov:wasRevisionOf relation from some newer prov:Entity to an earlier prov:Entity. For example, :draft_2 prov:wasRevisionOf :draft_1; prov:qualifiedRevision [ a prov:Revision; prov:entity :draft_1; :foo :bar ].

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Start.label: Start
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Start.description: An instance of prov:Start provides additional descriptions about the binary prov:wasStartedBy relation from some started prov:Activity to an prov:Entity that started it. For example, :foot_race prov:wasStartedBy :bang; prov:qualifiedStart [ a prov:Start; prov:entity :bang; :foo :bar; prov:atTime '2012-03-09T08:05:08-05:00'^^xsd:dateTime ] .

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Usage.label: Usage
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Usage.description: An instance of prov:Usage provides additional descriptions about the binary prov:used relation from some prov:Activity to an prov:Entity that it used. For example, :keynote prov:used :podium; prov:qualifiedUsage [ a prov:Usage; prov:entity :podium; :foo :bar ].

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#ServiceDescrip.label: ServiceDescription
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#ServiceDescrip.description: Type for a generic provenance query service. Mainly for use in RDF provenance query service descriptions, to facilitate discovery in linked data environments.

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#DirectQuerySer.label: ProvenanceService
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#DirectQuerySer.description: Type for a generic provenance query service. Mainly for use in RDF provenance query service descriptions, to facilitate discovery in linked data environments.

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Dictionary.label: Dictionary
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Dictionary.description: This concept allows for the provenance of the dictionary, but also of its constituents to be expressed. Such a notion of dictionary corresponds to a wide variety of concrete data structures, such as a maps or associative arrays.

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#actedOnBehalfO.label: actedOnBehalfOf
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#actedOnBehalfO.description: An object property to express the accountability of an agent towards another agent. The subordinate agent acted on behalf of the responsible agent in an actual activity.

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#hadActivity.label: hadActivity
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#hadActivity.description: The _optional_ Activity of an Influence, which used, generated, invalidated, or was the responsibility of some Entity. This property is _not_ used by ActivityInfluence (use prov:activity instead).

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#hadGeneration.label: hadGeneration
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#hadGeneration.description: The _optional_ Generation involved in an Entity's Derivation.

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#hadPlan.label: hadPlan
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#hadPlan.description: The _optional_ Plan adopted by an Agent in Association with some Activity. Plan specifications are out of the scope of this specification.

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#hadRole.label: hadRole
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#hadRole.description: The _optional_ Role that an Entity assumed in the context of an Activity. For example, :baking prov:used :spoon; prov:qualified [ a prov:Usage; prov:entity :spoon; prov:hadRole roles:mixing_implement ].

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#hadUsage.label: hadUsage
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#hadUsage.description: The _optional_ Usage involved in an Entity's Derivation.

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#influencer.label: influencer
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#influencer.description: Subproperties of prov:influencer are used to cite the object of an unqualified PROV-O triple whose predicate is a subproperty of prov:wasInfluencedBy (e.g. prov:used, prov:wasGeneratedBy). prov:influencer is used much like rdf:object is used.

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#qualifiedAssoc.label: qualifiedAssociation
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#qualifiedAssoc.description: If this Activity prov:wasAssociatedWith Agent :ag, then it can qualify the Association using prov:qualifiedAssociation [ a prov:Association;  prov:agent :ag; :foo :bar ].

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#qualifiedAttri.label: qualifiedAttribution
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#qualifiedAttri.description: If this Entity prov:wasAttributedTo Agent :ag, then it can qualify how it was influenced using prov:qualifiedAttribution [ a prov:Attribution;  prov:agent :ag; :foo :bar ].

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#qualifiedCommu.label: qualifiedCommunication
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#qualifiedCommu.description: If this Activity prov:wasInformedBy Activity :a, then it can qualify how it was influenced using prov:qualifiedCommunication [ a prov:Communication;  prov:activity :a; :foo :bar ].

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#qualifiedDeleg.label: qualifiedDelegation
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#qualifiedDeleg.description: If this Agent prov:actedOnBehalfOf Agent :ag, then it can qualify how with prov:qualifiedResponsibility [ a prov:Responsibility;  prov:agent :ag; :foo :bar ].

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#qualifiedDeriv.label: qualifiedDerivation
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#qualifiedDeriv.description: If this Entity prov:wasDerivedFrom Entity :e, then it can qualify how it was derived using prov:qualifiedDerivation [ a prov:Derivation;  prov:entity :e; :foo :bar ].

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#qualifiedEnd.label: qualifiedEnd
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#qualifiedEnd.description: If this Activity prov:wasEndedBy Entity :e1, then it can qualify how it was ended using prov:qualifiedEnd [ a prov:End;  prov:entity :e1; :foo :bar ].

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#qualifiedGener.label: qualifiedGeneration
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#qualifiedGener.description: If this Activity prov:generated Entity :e, then it can qualify how it performed the Generation using prov:qualifiedGeneration [ a prov:Generation;  prov:entity :e; :foo :bar ].

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#qualifiedInflu.label: qualifiedInfluence
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#qualifiedInflu.description: Because prov:qualifiedInfluence is a broad relation, the more specific relations (qualifiedCommunication, qualifiedDelegation, qualifiedEnd, etc.) should be used when applicable.

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#qualifiedInval.label: qualifiedInvalidation
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#qualifiedInval.description: If this Entity prov:wasInvalidatedBy Activity :a, then it can qualify how it was invalidated using prov:qualifiedInvalidation [ a prov:Invalidation;  prov:activity :a; :foo :bar ].

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#qualifiedPrima.label: qualifiedPrimarySource
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#qualifiedPrima.description: If this Entity prov:hadPrimarySource Entity :e, then it can qualify how using prov:qualifiedPrimarySource [ a prov:PrimarySource; prov:entity :e; :foo :bar ].

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#qualifiedQuota.label: qualifiedQuotation
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#qualifiedQuota.description: If this Entity prov:wasQuotedFrom Entity :e, then it can qualify how using prov:qualifiedQuotation [ a prov:Quotation;  prov:entity :e; :foo :bar ].

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#qualifiedRevis.label: qualifiedRevision
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#qualifiedRevis.description: If this Entity prov:wasRevisionOf Entity :e, then it can qualify how it was revised using prov:qualifiedRevision [ a prov:Revision;  prov:entity :e; :foo :bar ].

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#qualifiedStart.label: qualifiedStart
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#qualifiedStart.description: If this Activity prov:wasStartedBy Entity :e1, then it can qualify how it was started using prov:qualifiedStart [ a prov:Start;  prov:entity :e1; :foo :bar ].

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#qualifiedUsage.label: qualifiedUsage
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#qualifiedUsage.description: If this Activity prov:used Entity :e, then it can qualify how it used it using prov:qualifiedUsage [ a prov:Usage; prov:entity :e; :foo :bar ].

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#used.label: used
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#used.description: A prov:Entity that was used by this prov:Activity. For example, :baking prov:used :spoon, :egg, :oven .

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#wasAssociatedW.label: wasAssociatedWith
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#wasAssociatedW.description: An prov:Agent that had some (unspecified) responsibility for the occurrence of this prov:Activity.

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#wasAttributedT.label: wasAttributedTo
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#wasAttributedT.description: Attribution is the ascribing of an entity to an agent.

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#wasDerivedFrom.label: wasDerivedFrom
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#wasDerivedFrom.description: The more specific subproperties of prov:wasDerivedFrom (i.e., prov:wasQuotedFrom, prov:wasRevisionOf, prov:hadPrimarySource) should be used when applicable.

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#wasEndedBy.label: wasEndedBy
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#wasEndedBy.description: End is when an activity is deemed to have ended. An end may refer to an entity, known as trigger, that terminated the activity.

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#wasInfluencedB.label: wasInfluencedBy
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#wasInfluencedB.description: Because prov:wasInfluencedBy is a broad relation, its more specific subproperties (e.g. prov:wasInformedBy, prov:actedOnBehalfOf, prov:wasEndedBy, etc.) should be used when applicable.

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#wasInformedBy.label: wasInformedBy
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#wasInformedBy.description: An activity a2 is dependent on or informed by another activity a1, by way of some unspecified entity that is generated by a1 and used by a2.

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#wasQuotedFrom.label: wasQuotedFrom
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#wasQuotedFrom.description: An entity is derived from an original entity by copying, or 'quoting', some or all of it.

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#wasRevisionOf.label: wasRevisionOf
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#wasRevisionOf.description: A revision is a derivation that revises an entity into a revised version.

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#wasStartedBy.label: wasStartedBy
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#wasStartedBy.description: Start is when an activity is deemed to have started. A start may refer to an entity, known as trigger, that initiated the activity.

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#has_anchor.label: has_anchor
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#has_anchor.description: Indicates anchor URI for a potentially dynamic resource instance.

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#has_provenance.label: has_provenance
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#has_provenance.description: Indicates a provenance-URI for a resource; the resource identified by this property presents a provenance record about its subject or anchor resource.

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#has_query_serv.label: hasProvenanceService
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#has_query_serv.description: Indicates a provenance query service that can access provenance related to its subject or anchor resource.

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#describesServi.label: describesService
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#describesServi.description: relates a generic provenance query service resource (type prov:ServiceDescription) to a specific query service description (e.g. a prov:DirectQueryService or a sd:Service).

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#pingback.label: provenance pingback
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#pingback.description: Relates a resource to a provenance pingback service that may receive additional provenance links about the resource.

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#asInBundle.label: asInBundle
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#asInBundle.description:
prov:asInBundle is used to specify which bundle the general entity of a prov:mentionOf property is described.

When :x prov:mentionOf :y and :y is described in Bundle :b, the triple :x prov:asInBundle :b is also asserted to cite the Bundle in which :y was described.

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#mentionOf.label: mentionOf
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#mentionOf.description:
prov:mentionOf is used to specialize an entity as described in another bundle. It is to be used in conjuction with prov:asInBundle.

prov:asInBundle is used to cite the Bundle in which the generalization was mentioned.

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#atTime.label: atTime
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#atTime.description: The time at which an InstantaneousEvent occurred, in the form of xsd:dateTime.

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#endedAtTime.label: endedAtTime
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#endedAtTime.description: The time at which an activity ended. See also prov:startedAtTime.

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#generatedAtTim.label: generatedAtTime
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#generatedAtTim.description: The time at which an entity was completely created and is available for use.

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#invalidatedAtT.label: invalidatedAtTime
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#invalidatedAtT.description: The time at which an entity was invalidated (i.e., no longer usable).

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#startedAtTime.label: startedAtTime
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#startedAtTime.description: The time at which an activity started. See also prov:endedAtTime.

http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#provenanceUriT.label: provenanceUriTemplate
http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#provenanceUriT.description: Relates a provenance service to a URI template string for constructing provenance-URIs.

query_patterns.name: Find entities generated by an activity
query_patterns.description: Find all entities produced by activities

query_patterns.name: Get all properties of an entity
query_patterns.description: Retrieve all properties and values for a specific entity

core_concepts: Activity - Actions that occur over time
main_relationships: wasGeneratedBy - Links entities to activities that created them
used - Links activities to entities they consumed
wasAssociatedWith - Links activities to responsible agents
wasDerivedFrom - Links entities in derivation chains
